    passage: 'Game theory, the mathematical study of strategic decision-making, has applications far beyond economics. Biologists use it to model animal behavior, including territorial disputes and mating strategies. Political scientists apply it to analyze voting patterns and international negotiations. Even computer scientists employ game theory to develop artificial intelligence systems that can make optimal decisions in competitive environments. The unifying insight is that whenever multiple agents interact and their outcomes depend on each other\'s choices, game theory provides a framework for analysis.',
